  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. A 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the severity of the offense and the defendant's background. Considering federal sentencing guidelines for similar white-collar crimes involving this amount, a period of 6 months in a minimum-security facility is appropriate to serve as a sufficient deterrent and punishment, allowing for probation to manage the remaining restitution obligations.",
